Contact support Cowabunga What frameworks do you integrate with? We currently offer support for ROS 2 and are actively working on adding support for other frameworks such as ROS 1, ARK, and Please ping us in the contact form if there is a particular framework you need What if I have a limited network? This was one of the problems that motivated us to build this We offer various checks in place to work around a limited Small snippets of data will be uploaded for you to get an understanding of what you collected, and you can decide if you want to upload it straight from the robot or bring the disk to your computer to How do you monitor events? We provide several mechanisms to monitor specific topics within your ROS 2 For example, if you want to record whenever model performance drops below a threshold (i.e. % confidence), you can register this information in our interface and it will produce a recording every moment this Can I preserve the data before an event? Yes, we provide the functionality to maintain a rolling buffer that will automatically be prepended to any recording triggered by an Will data be recorded when the robot is offline? Once the robot a connection to the internet, the metadata around each recording will be uploaded for you to view in our Can I monitor data on custom messages? All you have to do is register the message s How do I access the data? Any way you like: our web interface, our API, or your S3 We leave the choice up to Ready to take the plunge? therapy can improve mental health and performance, leading to increased clarity and Resilience Resilience is the ability to bounce back from setbacks and It’s what allows you to keep going even when things don’t go as planned, and to learn and grow from your But for many founders, resilience can be hard to come You may be so used to pushing yourself to the limit that you burn out quickly, or so focused on achieving perfection that you’re unable to cope with At Pioneer Mind, we help founders build resilience by providing executive Our coaches are experts at helping you develop the skills and strategies you need to stay focused, motivated, and resilient, no matter what life throws your Executive coaching can significantly improve mental fitness and performance, leading to increased productivity and In a study published in the Academy of Management, researchers found that coaching can improve leadership skills and performance, leading to higher levels of job satisfaction and Belonging Belonging is the feeling of being connected to others and to something bigger than It’s what allows you to feel supported, valued, and But for many founders, belonging can be hard to come You may be so focused on your business that you neglect your personal relationships, or so isolated in your work that you feel disconnected from the world around At Pioneer Mind, we help founders feel a sense of belonging by providing peer groups . Our peer groups are a safe and supportive space where you can connect with other founders who are facing similar challenges and Peer support can significantly improve mental fitness and performance, leading to increased and social In a study published in the Journal of Social and Clinical Psychology, researchers found that peer support can improve mental health and , leading to increased and social

Tecarfarin - Cadrenal Therapeutics, Skip to content Home About Us Company Overview Management Team Board of Directors Scientific Advisory Board Our Focus Research & Development Tecarfarin Clinical Trials Investors Overview Press Releases Stock Information SEC Filings Governance Email Alerts Contact Menu Home About Us Company Overview Management Team Board of Directors Scientific Advisory Board Our Focus Research & Development Tecarfarin Clinical Trials Investors Overview Press Releases Stock Information SEC Filings Governance Email Alerts Contact Tecarfarin A novel therapy with orphan drug indication for the treatment of ESRD + AFib We are focused on advancing the development of tecarfarin, a novel therapy with orphan drug indication for the prevention of systemic thromboembolism of cardiac origin in patients with renal disease and atrial fibrillation (ESRD + AFib). Tecarfarin is an anticoagulation drug with the potential to replace warfarin as the standard for care for patients with ESRD + Tecarfarin is a Phase , vitamin K antagonist (VKA), taken once a day as an oral anticoagulant like Tecarfarin, like warfarin, was designed to have the same and reversible VKA mechanism of action, but to be free of certain potentially clearance and interaction problems associated with Tecarfarin was developed using a retrometabolic drug design process which targets a different metabolic pathway from the one targeted by the most commonly prescribed We believe this may allow elimination by large capacity and tissue esterase pathways that exist throughout the body rather than just in the Thus giving tecarfarin a better safety profile and potentially eliminates specific side effects while maintaining or improving In , the Food & Drug Administration granted tecarfarin an Orphan Drug Designation for treating patients with renal disease and atrial Advancing Tecarfarin We are currently focused on advancing our pivotal Phase 3 trial for We believe tecarfarin has the potential to be a safer, more effective treatment option for individuals with ESRD + Read more Proven Safety Profile Tecarfarin has been evaluated in human clinical trials in more than a thousand In Phase 1, Phase 2 and Phase 2 3 clinical trials that have conducted thus far, tecarfarin has generally been in both healthy adult patients and patients with chronic kidney We have established that tecarfarin has a similar Mechanism of Action to that of warfarin, while also showing that tecarfarin’s elimination from the body was not affected by severe kidney Learn more Improved Metabolic Profile Drug metabolism refers to the process by which a drug is inactivated by the body and rendered easier to eliminate or to be cleared by the Most approved drugs which are prescribed for the treatment of thrombosis, are metabolized in the liver through a pathway known as the Cytochrome CYP450 system, or CYP450, by the enzymes known as CYP2C9 and By using a different metabolic pathway, tecarfarin eliminates or minimizes the CYP450 metabolism in the Patients taking multiple medications, or those with impaired kidney function, can experience an overload in the pathway, creating a bottleneck that often leads to insufficient clearance, which results in a toxic of one or more In some instances, patients taking multiple medications metabolized by the same CYP450 pathway may experience decreased efficacy of one or more of the medications due to rapid metabolism or increased drug effect and or toxicity due to enzyme Our product candidate tecarfarin was designed to follow a metabolic pathway distinct from the CYP450 pathway and is metabolized by both CYP450 and We believe this may allow elimination by large capacity and tissue esterase pathways that exist throughout the body rather than just in the Contact Cadrenal Therapeutics, North A1A Ponte Vedra, FL
